    "content_hash": "6eeccd975264e258",
    "department": "R\u0026D",
    "description": "ABOUT SAVVY WEALTH:\n\nWealth management is a $545 billion industry in the US, yet remains archaic and inefficient with low technology penetration. 75% of financial advisors don’t offer digital communication beyond email, and 62% still build financial plans manually in Excel. This leads to a poor client experience and results in financial advisors spending over 70% of their time on non-client facing, manual work.\n\nSavvy is changing that. We’re building the most advisor-centric platform in wealth management: a digital-first solution that modernizes human financial advice. Advisors who partner with Savvy tap into AI-powered software, automated sales and marketing, and seamless back office workflows to scale faster and spend more time with clients.\n\nWe’ve raised over $105M to date from Thrive Capital, Index Ventures, Canvas Ventures, Mark Casady (former LPL Financial CEO), and other top-tier investors. Our team is made up of repeat founders and operators who’ve helped build Airbnb, Square, Brex, Carta, Facebook, $200B+ RIAs, and more.\n\nSavvy is at a pivotal point in its growth trajectory, having established strong product-market fit in providing a modern platform to financial advisors. We’ve surpassed $5.1 billion in AUM in less than three years, grown 600%+ in the last 18 months, and are entering the next phase of the company which involves rapid expansion of our product offering and continued revenue growth. Come help us scale!\n\nThe Role:\n\nWe’re looking for an experienced Engineering Manager to join our growing team. You’ll play a critical role in building, delivering, and scaling Savvy’s product. This is a hands-on management position: you’ll lead a team of passionate product-focused engineers while also diving into projects, collaborating closely with product, design, and go-to-market teams. You’ll learn how our business works, what our financial advisors and valuable clients need from us, and connect your engineering team’s work directly to business impact.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n - Drive execution \u0026 delivery: own technical project management, ensure projects are well scoped, deadlines are met, and quality is high.\n\n - Partner closely with our product and design teams to scope project feasibility and estimates.\n\n - Be a force multiplier: unblock engineers, help them grow, and maintain a high-performing culture that’s accountable to impact and delivery.\n\n - Lead \u0026 grow an engineering team (6+ direct reports), providing coaching, feedback, and career development, as well as managing performance, hiring, and when needed, making tough calls.\n\n - Wear multiple hats: step into product leadership when needed, meet with customers and prospects, and collaborate cross-functionally with sales, operations, compliance, and leadership.\n\n - Shape our engineering culture: help us scale from Series B to beyond, putting the right processes in place without heavy bureaucracy. Make sure your team feels empowered to deliver impact at high velocity.\n\nMust have:\n\n - 3+ years as an engineering manager at a mid-size, scaling startup (typically Series A–C), managing both technical execution and people (performance, hiring, firing).\n\n - Managed a team of at least 4-6+ engineers directly.\n\n - Background of 3+ years as a fullstack or backend engineer so that you are strong enough to dive into technical details, guide system design decisions, and mentor your team.\n\n - A delivery \u0026 execution-focused mindset, with clear awareness of your impact as an engineering leader.\n\n - Passion for enabling teams while holding them accountable for execution.\n\n - Experience on product-focused teams (shipping user-facing features) vs. solely infrastructure/platform teams.\n\n - Excited to grow with Savvy from Series B to later stages.\n\nNice to have:\n\n - Experience leading hybrid teams (we are a mix of in-person + remote across NYC and LatAm time zones).\n\n - Fintech or other compliance-heavy industry experience.\n\n - Exposure to infrastructure, data, or related technical areas.\n\n - Interest in being a future founder. Savvy can expose you to incredible detail on how scaling businesses grow, operate, and break.\n\n\nBENEFITS:\n\n - Competitive salary and equity package\n\n - Unlimited PTO + paid company holidays\n\n - Access to holistic medical, dental, and vision plans\n\n - Company 401(k), Commuter, and HSA/FSA plans\n\n - NYC office in the heart of Manhattan\n\n - Lunch and snacks provided in the office\n\n - Access to virtual mental health care (Spring Health), vision related benefits (XP Health), and health concierge (Rightway) to help you find the right care\n\n - Access to counseling for stress management, dependent care, nutrition, fitness, legal, and financial issues (Guardian WorkLifeMatters EAP)",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
